    Personal Project

FADE IN:

EXT. CITY SKYLINE - DAY

A sprawling metropolitan cityscape. The sun rises over the buildings, painting everything in warm golden light.

We push in on one building in particular — an unremarkable apartment complex.

INT. APARTMENT - MORNING

A modest but lived-in apartment. Coffee brews on the counter. Papers are scattered across a small desk.

PROTAGONIST sits at the desk, staring at a blank page.

PROTAGONIST
(muttering to self)
Just start writing. How hard can it be?

The cursor blinks mockingly on the screen.

PROTAGONIST (CONT'D)
Apparently very hard.

A KNOCK at the door.

PROTAGONIST
(calling out)
It's open!

The door swings open to reveal BEST FRIEND, carrying two coffees and a grocery bag.

BEST FRIEND
You look terrible.

PROTAGONIST
Thanks. I've been up since four.

BEST FRIEND
(setting down coffees)
Writing?

PROTAGONIST
Trying to.

BEST FRIEND
What's it about?

PROTAGONIST
(beat)
I have absolutely no idea.

They share a look. Then burst out laughing.

CUT TO:

